# Append this block to your project's AGENTS.md (or copy into your Codex CLI instructions).
# Codex CLI has no hook system, so this is enforced as a behavioral instruction.

## Security review at end of feature work

Before declaring a feature complete, opening a PR, or pushing changes:

1. If any of the following changed in this branch — endpoints/routes, auth or RBAC logic,
   frontend rendering, outbound HTTP fetches, dependencies, security-relevant config — run
   the 8-point security check from `skills/Security Assessment/Security-reviewr/security-reviewer.md`
   on the diff.

2. For a thorough pre-release pass, run the comprehensive assessment described in
   `skills/Security Assessment/security-assessment/SKILL.md`.

3. For new architecture or sensitive features, run the threat model in
   `skills/Security Assessment/threat-modeling/SKILL.md`.

Output a short findings list with severity (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW), file:line, evidence
snippet, and recommended fix. If clean, say so explicitly and list residual risks.

Read-only — do not modify code as part of the review itself; propose fixes instead.
